# abfv local configuration - copy to `.env` and edit for your machine.
# `main` loads `.env` at startup; clap reads these via its `env = ...` args.
# Real environment variables (e.g. those baked into the Docker image) win over
# anything set here.

# Structure prediction runs in-process via ONNX (ort) — no Python needed.
# Both default to vendored, in-repo paths; override only if you relocate them:
#   ABFV_ONNX       the ABodyBuilder3 model exported to ONNX (vendored/abb3.onnx)
#   ABFV_ORT_DYLIB  libonnxruntime.so dlopen'd at runtime (load-dynamic)
# ABFV_ONNX=/path/to/abb3.onnx
# ABFV_ORT_DYLIB=/opt/onnxruntime/lib/libonnxruntime.so

# Python is used only for the matplotlib `visualize` step.
ABFV_PYTHON=/path/to/abodybuilder3/.venv/bin/python

# The freesasa binary is vendored in-repo (vendored/) with a relative default.
# Override ABFV_FREESASA only if you keep it elsewhere.